That's how Mincy started, one of the best players Puerto Rico had.
Bartow then recommended Raymond Gausse, who was naturalized and who was one of the best shooters.
I remember him saying that if Mincy had allowed Bayamon to win a championship, Gausse was going to help us try to win another one.
He was pleased with the Vaqueros Championship with Gausse, but only at a distance since in 1988 he was already the big manitou of the federation.
At that time, he preferred to take advantage of Mincy's duties and those in the national team.
I remember when we first won it in the United States at the pre-olympic tournament in Mexico in 1989.
Then there was the 1990 World Cup, where we arrived 4th and where we should have won the bronze medal if this Canadian judge hadn't let us play the last game, Reyes said.
The 1990 World Cup is the best national team you've ever seen?
She is one of the best, just like the one who beat the Dream Team at the 2004 Olympic Games.
But my favorite is that of the Pan American Games in Cuba in 1991, when we won the gold and we razed the U.S. team, which was quite similar to the one that won the bronze in the World Cup.
